{"title":"VYNL Bikes Relaunches: New Ownership, plus new Road and Gravel Disc frames","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/09/vynl-bikes-relaunches/","date":1625871617000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>After a year-long hiatus, Boulder, CO’s VYNL Bikes is back. New ownership seeks to revive the company by adding two new frame designs but maintains the brand’s characteristic stripped-down approach. Ownership is also intent on keeping the company entirely U.S.-based, from fabrication to delivery.</p><figure id=\"attachment_264784\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-264784\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x323/rscb25/ng:webp/ngcb25\" alt=\"vynl bike gravel frame\" width=\"1998\" height=\"1334\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1998w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-800x534.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-768x513.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-1536x1026.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-696x465.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-1068x713.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-1920x1282.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-629x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 629w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1998px) 100vw, 1998px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x323/rscb25/ng:webp/ngcb25\" ezoid=\"0.7496848107248704\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1998w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-800x534.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-768x513.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-1536x1026.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-696x465.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-1068x713.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-1920x1282.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162728/VYNLBikes-Gravel-SageGreen-Back-Angle-Profile-629x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 629w\"><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-264784\">VYNL Gravel Disc</figcaption></figure><p>Road and gravel disc frames join the original road rim design for the relaunch. Though the VYNL stable will expand, new co-owner Max Clauson says the company will maintain its strict manufacturing standards.</p><blockquote><p>“The VYNL lineup may expand but one thing will remain,” Clauson said. “We’re absolutely staying committed to fast bikes with aggressive race geometry and careful, skilled manufacturing.”</p></blockquote><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162907/VYNL-Frame-Raw-Toptube-Badge-31.jpg\" alt=\"viny bike road disc frame detail\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09162907/VYNL-Frame-Raw-Toptube-Badge-31.jpg 2000w,https://bikerumor.c