e-Badge-3.jpg 2000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09163340/VYNL-Frame-Pink-Seattube-Badge-3-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09163340/VYNL-Frame-Pink-Seattube-Badge-3-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09163340/VYNL-Frame-Pink-Seattube-Badge-3-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09163340/VYNL-Frame-Pink-Seattube-Badge-3-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09163340/VYNL-Frame-Pink-Seattube-Badge-3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09163340/VYNL-Frame-Pink-Seattube-Badge-3-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09163340/VYNL-Frame-Pink-Seattube-Badge-3-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09163340/VYNL-Frame-Pink-Seattube-Badge-3-1920x1280.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09163340/VYNL-Frame-Pink-Seattube-Badge-3-630x420.jpg 630w\"></p><p>The localization strategy may also help engage VYNL Bikes’ community. “From our headquarters here in Boulder, we’re remaining committed to 100% USA-made frames and leveraging local talent as much as possible,” Max explains. “Not only is it great to support local craftspeople, but we can ensure quality and develop new prototype ideas on the fly.”</p><figure id=\"attachment_264786\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-264786\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09163236/VYNLBikes-Road-White-Fron